        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 4:26AM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 426 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fennville, or 12 miles south of Holland, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Holland...             Fennville...           Saugatuck...
Dorr...                Ganges...              Hamilton...
Douglas...             Burnips...             Macatawa...
Glenn...               Castle Park...         Saugatuck Dunes SP...
Overisel...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
